1. Children Prop
Use children to pass content inside a component
JSX
function Card({ children, title }) {
  return (
    <div className="card">
      {title && <h3>{title}</h3>}
      <div>{children}</div>
    </div>
  );
}
Usage:
JSX
<Card title="Hello">
  <p>Content here</p>
</Card>
👉 Anything between <Card>...</Card> becomes children
🏗️ 2. Layout Component
Wrap pages with shared UI (Header, Footer, etc.)
JSX
function Layout({ children }) {
  return (
    <>
      <Header />
      <main>{children}</main>
      <Footer />
    </>
  );
}
Usage:
JSX
<Layout>
  <h1>Home</h1>
  <PostList />
</Layout>
👉 Layout stays same, only inner content changes
🔀 3. Conditional Rendering Patterns
✅ AND (&&)
Show only if true
JSX
{user && <p>Hi {user.name}</p>}
🔁 Ternary (if/else)
JSX
{user ? <p>Welcome</p> : <p>Please login</p>}
🚪 Early Return
JSX
if (!user) return <p>Please login</p>;
return <p>Welcome {user.name}</p>;
